  <description><![CDATA[<p>A city-style hotel in the centre of Interlaken. At the high-rise Hotel Metropole, you can enjoy all the convenience and trappings of a stylish metropolitan hotel to an impressive mountain backdrop.</p>
<h2>Easy access to mountains, lakes, and walking trails</h2>
<p>Each of the hotel's 96 bedrooms has spectacular views over Interlaken and the surrounding mountains, and you'll find a huge range of activities to enjoy on your doorstep. Just over a ten-minute walk from the hotel is the Harder Kulm funicular. From the top you can see both Lake Brienz and Lake Thun, enjoy the pretty circular walking trail, and watch spectacular sunsets at the end of the day.</p>
<p>If you're keen to see more of the area then a short bus ride will have you beside the cool, clear waters of the beautiful lakes - Brienz and Thun. Interlaken West train station is just a seven-minute walk, and the bus stop's 100 metres from the hotel - great options for exploring the wider Jungfrau region.</p>
<h2>A 24hr gym, and a garden terrace with panoramic views</h2>
<p>If you've still got energy to burn after a day's exploring there's a 24-hour fitness centre in the hotel, and guests also have free use of the neighbouring Tennis Club's courts. For something a little more relaxing head to the sauna to ease tired muscles, or escape to the lovely first-floor garden terrace offers a quiet place to read a book and enjoy the panoramic views.</p>
<p>The first-floor lounge has free tea and coffee-making facilities, and if you fancy something stronger you can head to the stylish Metro Bar, with its vaulted glass roof and grand piano.</p>]]></description>
